IMPLEMENT CONTROL STATEMENTS

SOLUTION-

Control statements control the flow of any program and tells whether the particular program will get executed or not.
They are:-

IF-ELSE 
Syntax:
if (condition) 
{ 
Statement 1; //if it's true
}
else
{
Statement 2; //otherwise
}

Implementation:
public static void main(String args[])
{
int a = 100;
if (a > 20)
System.out.println("a is greater than 20");
else
System.out.println("a is less than 20");
}
}

WHILE
Syntax:
while (condition)
{
statement;
}

Implementation:

public static void main(String args[])
{
int i = 5;
while (i <= 15)
{
System.out.println(i);
i = i+5;
}
}

DO-WHILE
Syntax:
do
{
//code to be executed
}
while(condition);

Implementation:
public static void main(String args[]) 
{ 
int i = 5; 
do 
{ 
System.out.println(i); 
i = i+1; 
} while (i <= 15); 
} 

FOR
Syntax:
for (initialization; condition; increment/decrement)
{
statement;
}

Implementation:
public static void main(String args[])
{
for (int i = 1; i <= 10; i++)
System.out.println(i);
}
